# Exploration: od

## Rounds
  round 0: 51 isolated cumulative, 6 identical in round (discovery)
  round 1: 76 isolated cumulative, 8 identical in round (refinement)
  round 2: 76 isolated cumulative, 14 identical in round (refinement)

## Distinguished: 20/21 flags
  19 solo (unique behavior)
  1 via combination only
  1 behavioral aliases detected

Aliases: -A = --address-radix, -N = --read-bytes, -j = --skip-bytes, -t = --format, -v = --output-duplicates

## Solo (unique behavior)
  --endian  # swap input bytes according the specified order
  --strings
  --traditional  # accept arguments in third form above
  -A  # output format for file offsets; RADIX is one
  -N  # limit dump to BYTES input bytes
  -S
  -a  # same as -t a,  select named characters, ignoring high-order bit
  -b  # same as -t o1, select octal bytes
  -c  # same as -t c,  select printable characters or backslash escapes
  -d  # same as -t u2, select unsigned decimal 2-byte units
  -f  # same as -t fF, select floats
  -i  # same as -t dI, select decimal ints
  -j  # skip BYTES input bytes first
  -l  # same as -t dL, select decimal longs
  -o  # same as -t o2, select octal 2-byte units
  -s  # same as -t d2, select decimal 2-byte units
  -t  # select output format or formats
  -v  # do not use * to mark line suppression
  -x  # same as -t x2, select hexadecimal 2-byte units

## Via combination (distinguishable when paired)
  --width  e.g. "-b" "--width" "input.txt"

